Former Vice President Atiku Abubakar has condoled with the Governor of Oyo State, Seyi Makinde over the death of his mother. DAILY POST had reported that the Governor lost his mother, Mrs. Abigail Makinde in the early hours of Thursday. Reacting, the former Vice President in a tweet via his Twitter account sent his condolences to the Governor and his family. “My heartfelt condolences to Seyi Makinde on the loss of your beloved mother. “The loss of a mother comes with deep emotional pains, and I join in the prayers for you and your family to find strength and comfort in God. “May her soul rest in perfect peace,” he said.